Definition: fraught with danger
Example: dangerous waters; a parlous journey on stormy seas; a perilous voyage across the Atlantic in a small boat; the precarious life of an undersea diver; dangerous surgery followed by a touch-and-go recovery
Synonyms: perilous, noun, state, peril, act, perilousness, precarious, attribute, precariousness, touch-and-go, fraught, with, danger, dangerous, waters, a, journey, on, stormy, seas, voyage, across, the, Atlantic, in, small, boat, life, of, an, undersea, diver, surgery, followed, by, recovery
Category: adj.all
